result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Demand for Discovery and Inspection - Prosecutor

records.addlTxt:
10:12 AM Defendant Kimberly Hope Semanko in court.  Attorney Ryan Anthony Reid appeared by video for Kimberly Hope Semanko.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. State calls witness, Taylor Wendt, Officer City of Superior. Witness sworn and testifies. State-direct examination of witness. October 26, 2022, City of Superior, Douglas County Wisconsin. Witness identifies Defendant. Record reflects identification.  Attorney Reid cross examines witness. Objection, sustained. Objection, relevance, sustained. Attorney Reid makes statements, sustained. Continued questioning. Objection relevance, sustained. Objection, relevance, sustained. State rests. 
State makes argument for bind over. Attorney Reid makes argument for dismissal of Count 1. Motion to dismiss denied. Court finds probable cause and binds the Defendant over for Arraignment. 
Court reminds the Defendant of their bail conditions. Defendant orally confirms they have received date and time of hearing and confirms they will attend. Defendant provided notice.
Arraignment scheduled for January 30, 2023 at 11:00 am.

1:43 PM Defendant Kimberly Hope Semanko appeared by video, in custody. Attorney Ryan Reid appears with defendant.  Attorney Allison Cogbill in court for State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case. Address verified. Acknowledges complaint, waives reading, pleads not guilty. Court accepts pleas. 
State requests $500 cash, no use of drugs, no contact with Walmart in Superior. Cites prior FTA's.
Attorney Reid asks for signature bond or lower cash bond of $200. Lives at current address for 20 years. Has family support.
Court orders $500 cash, with conditions of no contact with Walmart in Superior, no use or possession of drugs or drug related paraphernalia
Preliminary hearing scheduled for November 2, 2022 at 10:15 am.
